[[Image:Diccionario Enciclopédico Salvat Universal.JPG|thumb|240px|Diccionario Enciclopédico Salvat Universal.]]
'''''Enciclopedia Salvat''''', long title ''Diccionario Enciclopédico Salvat Universal'' is a [[Spanish language|Spanish]]-language encyclopedia compiled and published by [[Salvat Editores|Editorial Salvat]] (Salvat Editores), a well-known house in development and publication of dictionaries and reference works on various levels.

The 20-volume 16,000 page alphabetically arranged and illustrated encyclopedia focuses on the core areas of knowledge: [[Physics]], [[Chemistry]], [[Biology]], [[Ecology]], [[Mathematics]], [[Philosophy]] and [[Religion]], [[Medicine]], [[Language]] and [[Literature]], [[History]] and [[Geography]], [[Arts]], [[Technology]], [[IT]], etc. with related references wherever needed. The recent{{when|date=February 2016}} update also launched a unique system for summaries accompanied by a new design and layout.

