{|{{Infobox ship begin|infobox caption=''Eppleton Hall''}} {{Infobox ship image |Ship image=Eppleton Hall.jpg |Ship image size=300px |Ship caption=''Eppleton Hall'' in San Francisco }} {{Infobox ship career |Hide header= |Ship country= |Ship flag={{shipboxflag|UK|civil}} {{shipboxflag|USA|civil}} |Ship name= |Ship namesake= |Ship owner=*1914-1924 Lambton and Hetton Collieries Ltd *1924-1945 Lambton, Hetton & Joicey Collieries Ltd *1945-1964 France, Fenwick Tyne & Wear Co Ltd *1964-1967 Seaham Harbour Dock Co<ref name=Proud>{{cite book|last=Proud|first=John H F|title=150 Years of the Maltese Cross: The Story of Tyne, Blyth and Wear Tug Companies|publisher=Tyne & Wear Tugs Ltd|location=South Shields|year=1993|isbn=0-9522721-0-5|pages=211–214}}</ref> *1967-1979 [[Scott Newhall]]/Karl Kortum *1979 National Park Service |Ship operator= |Ship registry=*1914-1967 Newcastle upon Tyne<ref name=Proud/> *1969 San Francisco, California |Ship route= |Ship ordered= |Ship awarded= |Ship builder=[[Hepple and Company]], [[South Shields]] |Ship original cost= |Ship yard number=632<ref name=Proud/> |Ship way number= |Ship laid down= |Ship launched= |Ship sponsor= |Ship christened= |Ship completed=1914<ref name=Proud/> |Ship acquired= |Ship commissioned= |Ship recommissioned= |Ship decommissioned= |Ship maiden voyage= |Ship in service=1914-1967<ref name=Proud/> |Ship out of service= |Ship renamed= |Ship reclassified= |Ship refit= |Ship struck= |Ship reinstated= |Ship homeport= |Ship identification= |Ship motto= |Ship nickname= |Ship honours= |Ship honors= |Ship captured= |Ship fate= |Ship status=[[Museum ship]] at [[San Francisco|San Francisco, California]]<ref name=Proud/> |Ship notes= |Ship badge= }} {{Infobox ship characteristics |Hide header= |Header caption= |Ship class= |Ship type=[[Tugboat]] |Ship tonnage={{GRT|166|disp=long}}<ref name=Proud/> |Ship displacement= |Ship tons burthen= |Ship length={{convert|100.5|ft|abbr=on}} |Ship beam={{convert|21.1|ft|abbr=on}} |Ship height= |S